════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Springfield line terminus, family demand, and a retail hub on the western corridor.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Richlands sits approximately 15km west of Brisbane CBD and occupies a distinctive position in the western corridor: it is the only suburb in this part of Brisbane that sits directly on Richlands Station, the terminus of the Springfield Central rail line. That rail access is the suburb's clearest differentiator for buyers who need to commute by train but require a price point that has moved beyond Forest Lake and Oxley. Families who have been patient about finding value in the western corridor increasingly land on Richlands as the answer.
    </p>
