<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:40px 24px 80px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Richlands.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Richlands?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Block size, proximity to Richlands Station on the Springfield Central line, and whether the property sits in a newer estate or the older established section are the key value drivers. Homes in the newer residential estates attract families and owner-occupiers who want turn-key presentation, while larger older blocks draw investors and buyers who value land. The park-and-ride at Richlands Station adds a commuter premium to properties within easy reach of the station precinct.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Richlands?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Richlands homes typically sell within 28 to 45 days. The buyer pool is a healthy mix of families, first home buyers and investors, each with different finance timelines. Newer estate homes with strong street appeal and proximity to the station tend to move quickest. Older homes on larger blocks can attract competitive bidding when marketed well to buyers who understand the land value on offer.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Richlands?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Richlands is a practical, well-connected western Brisbane suburb. The Springfield Central line provides direct rail to the CBD, and the large park-and-ride facility at Richlands Station means the suburb also serves as a transport hub for surrounding areas. The IKEA and major retail precinct on the eastern edge covers everyday needs. Neighbouring Forest Lake has a sizeable lake and recreational parklands that residents access regularly. For families, the combination of newer estates, school catchments and motorway connectivity makes Richlands a genuinely functional place to live at a price point that remains accessible.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Richlands a good suburb to sell in?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Richlands has a consistent and growing buyer market. As Forest Lake and Oxley have strengthened in price, buyers have progressively moved toward Richlands seeking comparable connectivity at a lower entry point. The Springfield Central terminus is the suburb's most significant differentiator in the western corridor, and that infrastructure is not replicated in nearby Inala, Doolandella or Durack. The combination of rail access, motorway proximity and a commercial retail hub makes Richlands a sound suburb to sell in when presented correctly.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

